# LiveKit Migration Context

This project migrated from mediasoup to LiveKit for WebRTC media routing. Socket.IO is retained for non-media signaling (sketches, emotes, peer info).

## Architecture

### Media (LiveKit)
- `src/hooks/useLivekitRoom.js` ‚Äî connects to LiveKit, generates per-tab session ID to avoid identity collisions across browser tabs
- `src/app/api/livekit/token/route.js` ‚Äî Next.js API route that validates Supabase JWT, checks user_roles/collaborator_ids, returns LiveKit access token with role-based `canPublish`
- Token identity format: `{userId}-{tabSessionId}`, real userId stored in participant metadata
- Anonymous users (Supabase anonymous auth) get `canPublish: false, canSubscribe: true`
- `useLivekitRoom` uses `waitForSession()` to handle race condition between anonymous sign-in and token fetch

### Signaling (Socket.IO ‚Äî kept for backward compat)
- `src/hooks/useSignalingSocket.js` ‚Äî standalone socket.io-client connection, sets `window.socket` for p5.js sketch compatibility
- Events preserved: relay, mousePosition, peerInfo, savePeerData, serverTime, joinLobby/leaveLobby, emote, counts
- `server/index.js` ‚Äî Express + Socket.IO server, mediasoup removed, all socket handlers unchanged

### Context Provider
- `src/components/RealtimeContext.js` ‚Äî provides `room` (LiveKit), `socket` (Socket.IO), `broadcastVideoStream`, `broadcastAudioStream`, `peerVideoStreams`, `peerAudioStreams`
- Track mapping: `video-broadcast`, `audio-broadcast`, `peer-video`, `peer-audio` track names
- Peer identification: extract `userId` from `participant.metadata` (not `participant.identity`, which includes tab session suffix)

## Track Publishing

### Broadcast (BroadcastStreamControls)
- Video: 3 Mbps max, 30fps, VP8 with simulcast (360p + 180p layers)
- Audio: 128 Kbps, dtx disabled, RED enabled ‚Äî optimized for pro audio interfaces (Scarlett, etc.)
- `unpublishTrack` uses `stopOnUnpublish: false` to keep MediaStreamTrack alive for re-publishing
- Audio processing (echo cancellation, noise suppression, auto gain) is force-disabled

### Lobby (peer-to-peer in 3D space)
- Publishes `peer-video` (80 Kbps) and `peer-audio` tracks
- Distance-based selective subscription via `pub.setSubscribed()`

## Capture (useUserMedia.js)
- Raw `navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia()` ‚Äî NOT LiveKit's track creation APIs (Phase 2 candidate)
- Video: 1280x720 ideal, 30fps ideal
- Audio: stereo (channelCount ideal 2), all processing disabled
- `window.broadcastVideoStream` and `window.broadcastAudioStream` set as globals for sketch compatibility

